      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): forward web_search_options through OpenAI-compatible chat completions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nForward `web_search_options` (`search_context_size`, `user_location`) from the OpenAI-compatible HTTP chat completions endpoint through to the provider-native web search injection layer.\n\n### What this does\n\n- **Gateway layer** (`src/gateway/openai-http.ts`): Parses and validates `web_search_options` from the chat completions request body. Supports `search_context_size: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\"` and OpenAI Chat-style `user_location { type: \"approximate\", city, country, region, timezone }`. Unknown fields or invalid values return `400 invalid_request_error`.\n- **Stream params type** (`src/agents/command/shared-types.ts`): Adds `NativeWebSearchStreamParams` type and `nativeWebSearch` field to `AgentStreamParams`.\n- **Extra params routing** (`src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.ts`): Marks `nativeWebSearch` as request-scoped (excluded from cache), validates model eligibility, and routes it to provider runtime wrappers. Fails explicitly with a clear error when `web_search_options` is requested but the selected backend cannot honor native search (wrong provider, web search disabled, non-OpenAI model, etc.).\n- **OpenAI provider** (`extensions/openai/native-web-search.ts`): Injects `search_context_size` and `user_location` into the `web_search` tool payload on available OpenAI Responses backends.\n- **Codex native search** (`src/agents/codex-native-web-search-core.ts`, `src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/openai.ts`): Same for Codex ChatGPT Responses backends, with request-scoped options overriding config defaults.\n- **Error normalization** (`src/gateway/openai-compat-errors.ts`): Maps native web search incompatibility errors to OpenAI-compatible `400 invalid_request_error` envelopes.\n- **Docs** (`docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md`): Documents the new `web_search_options` parameter.\n\n### Key behaviors\n\n- `web_search_options` does NOT select a managed OpenClaw search provider; it only customizes native OpenAI/Codex `web_search` when that native path is already allowed.\n- If `web_search_options` is requested but native search is unavailable (wrong provider, disabled, code mode active, tool policy denies), the run fails explicitly instead of silently falling back.\n- Request-scoped `nativeWebSearch` is not cached in the prepared extra params cache (matching `response_format` and `stop` behavior).\n- `user_location: null` can be used to clear any config-default location.\n\n\n## Verification\n\n- Local tests: `pnpm test src/gateway/openai-http.test.ts extensions/openai/openai-provider.test.ts src/agents/codex-native-web-search.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.provider-runtime.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.sampling.test.ts src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/openai.test.ts`\n- Result: **10 test files, 201 tests all passed**\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `web_search_options` submitted to the OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` HTTP endpoint are parsed on the real Gateway request path, forwarded into request-scoped native web search params for eligible OpenAI/Codex native search backends, and rejected with an OpenAI-compatible error when native web search cannot be honored.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw Gateway built from pre-rebase PR head `1185c1b861ff0b68ee3aed1c86776eb3fe010b08` (the live behavior proof commit). Current rebased and squashed PR head `0541376e632596fbd838a88d54ab5fba0b03f229` was verified with the focused test set, changed-file lint, and a full build. The live backend path was not rerun because the behavior-bearing diff is unchanged. The live proof used loopback HTTP, temporary config, existing redacted Codex login state, managed Codex app-server `0.139.0`, and eligible `openai/gpt-5.4-mini` (`openai-responses`). The same built Gateway was also exercised with an unsupported native-search backend for the negative path. No credentials, auth profiles, full session transcripts, or unredacted location values are included below.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false docs:list\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false build\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/openai-http.test.ts extensions/openai/openai-provider.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.provider-runtime.test.ts src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/openai.test.ts\n\n# Positive eligible-backend proof.\n# Temporary config enables gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions and selects\n# openai/gpt-5.4-mini with native web search enabled.\nOPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-web-search-proof/openclaw.json \\\n  node dist/index.js gateway run --bind loopback --port 19693 --auth none\n\n# Location values shown here are redacted from the actual request.\ncurl -sS -X POST http://127.0.0.1:19693/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'content-type: application/json' \\\n  --data '{\n    \"model\": \"openclaw\",\n    \"messages\": [{\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Use native web search to find the official OpenAI homepage. Reply with only the first result title and URL.\"\n    }],\n    \"web_search_options\": {\n      \"search_context_size\": \"low\",\n      \"user_location\": {\n        \"type\": \"approximate\",\n        \"approximate\": {\n          \"city\": \"<redacted-city>\",\n          \"region\": \"<redacted-region>\",\n          \"country\": \"US\",\n          \"timezone\": \"<redacted-timezone>\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- `docs:list` passed after bypassing the local dependency reconciliation prompt with `--config.verify-deps-before-run=false`.\n- `build` passed from the PR checkout.\n- Focused Vitest proof passed: 4 shards, 6 relevant test files, 143 tests.\n- The positive eligible-backend request returned `HTTP/1.1 200 OK`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"<redacted>\",\n  \"object\": \"chat.completion\",\n  \"model\": \"openclaw\",\n  \"choices\": [{\n    \"message\": {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"OpenAI | Research & Deployment\\nhttps://openai.com/\"\n    },\n    \"finish_reason\": \"stop\"\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n- The redacted Codex rollout recorded a completed native search event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"web_search_call\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"action\": {\n    \"type\": \"search\",\n    \"query\": \"OpenAI official homepage\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- The matching redacted OpenClaw trajectory recorded `provider=openai`, `modelId=gpt-5.4-mini`, `modelApi=openai-responses`, followed by `tool.call name=web_search` and `tool.result status=completed isError=false`.\n- The unsupported-backend request still returned the expected `400 invalid_request_error`: `web_search_options require native OpenAI/Codex web_search, but the selected model does not support native web_search`.\n- Codex source contract checked at sibling Codex SHA `dfd03ea`: `codex-rs/codex-api/src/search.rs` defines `SearchSettings.user_location` and `search_context_size`; `codex-rs/ext/web-search/src/extension.rs` enables the extension for OpenAI providers and maps both settings; `codex-rs/models-manager/models.json` marks `gpt-5.4-mini` with `supports_search_tool: true`.\n\nObserved result after fix: A real OpenAI-compatible HTTP request carrying `web_search_options` completed successfully through the eligible Codex/OpenAI Responses backend, executed native `web_search`, and returned the search result in a `200` chat-completion response. The negative unsupported-backend behavior remained an explicit OpenAI-compatible `400` instead of silently ignoring the request options.\n\nWhat was not tested: A separate direct API-key OpenAI Responses backend, live requests for every `search_context_size` value, `user_location: null`, cross-platform Crabbox/Testbox lanes, and Docker were not tested. Those option shapes and provider-payload mappings are covered by the focused tests above.\n",
